==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pitiable
<hw>Pit"i*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. OF.
<ets>pitiable</ets>, F. <ets>pitoyable</ets>.]</ety> <def>Deserving
pity; worthy of, or exciting, compassion; miserable; lamentable;
piteous; <as>as, <ex>pitiable</ex> persons; a <ex>pitiable</ex>
condition; <ex>pitiable</ex> wretchedness.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Sorrowful; woeful; sad. See
<er>Piteous</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Pit"i*a*ble*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>Pit"i*a*bly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pitier</ent>⟦br⟧
